Matching within escapable delimiters is not too hard. For instance this will match C-style escaped strings:<p><pre><code>    &quot;(\.|[^&quot;])*&quot;
</code></pre>
You just won&#x27;t be able to nest them. You&#x27;re either in a string or you aren&#x27;t. You&#x27;re never in a string inside another string.
